(8, 'Jean', '8 - Besoin d\'un plan B', '<h1>You don\'t know how to do any of those.</h1> <p>Then throw her in the laundry room, which will hereafter be referred to as \"the brig\". Actually, that\'s still true. No! Don\'t jump! I love this planet! I\'ve got wealth, fame, and access to the depths of sleaze that those things bring.</p> <p>It\'s a T. It goes \"tuh\". Dear God, they\'ll be killed on our doorstep! And there\'s no trash pickup until January 3rd. <strong>Spare me your space age technobabble, Attila the Hun!</strong> <em>I\'m a thing.</em> Belligerent and numerous.</p> <h2>Daylight and everything.</h2> <p>You don\'t know how to do any of those. We\'re rescuing ya. Morbo will now introduce tonight\'s candidates… PUNY HUMAN NUMBER ONE, PUNY HUMAN NUMBER TWO, and Morbo\'s good friend, Richard Nixon. Who am I making this out to?</p> <ol> <li>I feel like I was mauled by Jesus.</li> <li>You guys go on without me! I\'m going to go… look for more stuff to steal!</li> <li>We don\'t have a brig.</li> </ol> <h3>Doomsday device? Ah, now the ball\'s in Farnsworth\'s court!</h3> <p>Humans dating robots is sick. You people wonder why I\'m still single? It\'s \'cause all the fine robot sisters are dating humans! Switzerland is small and neutral! We are more like Germany, ambitious and misunderstood!</p> <ul> <li>Take me to your leader!</li> <li>Oh God, what have I done?</li> <li>Bite my shiny metal ass.</li> </ul>', '2020-09-01 06:42:51', '2020-09-04 06:42:51', 1, '/img/img-chapter-8.png'),
(52, 'Jean', '15 - Et maintenant ?', '<p>Mrs. <strong>Krabappel and Principal Skinner were in the closet making babies and I saw one of the babies and then the baby looked at me.</strong> <em>Bart, with $10,000 we\'d be millionaires!</em> We could buy all kinds of useful things like…love!</p>\r\n<h2>I don\'t like being outdoors, Smithers. For one thing, there\'s too many fat children.</h2>\r\n<p>Your questions have become more redundant and annoying than the last three \"Highlander\" movies. How could you?! Haven\'t you learned anything from that guy who gives those sermons at church? Captain Whatshisname? We live in a society of laws! Why do you think I took you to all those Police Academy movies? For fun? Well, I didn\'t hear anybody laughing, did you? Except at that guy who made sound effects. Makes sound effects and laughs. Where was I? Oh yeah! Stay out of my booze.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>I stand by my racial slur.</li>\r\n<li>Fame was like a drug. But what was even more like a drug were the drugs.</li>\r\n<li>Oh, everything looks bad if you remember it.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>I like my beer cold, my TV loud and my homosexuals flaming.</h3>\r\n<p>You don\'t like your job, you don\'t strike. You go in every day and do it really half-assed. That\'s the American way. Son, when you participate in sporting events, it\'s not whether you win or lose: it\'s how drunk you get.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Your guilty consciences may make you vote Democratic, but secretly you all yearn for a Republican president to lower taxes, brutalize criminals, and rule you like a king!</li>\r\n<li>Here\'s to alcohol, the cause of — and solution to — all life\'s problems.</li>\r\n<li>Shoplifting is a victimless crime. Like punching someone in the dark.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2020-09-04 12:47:26', '2020-09-04 12:52:11', 1, '/img/img-chapter-3.png'),
(9, 'Jean', '9 - Quel pays fascinant', '<h1>You don\'t know how to do any of those.</h1> <p>Then throw her in the laundry room, which will hereafter be referred to as \"the brig\". Actually, that\'s still true. No! Don\'t jump! I love this planet! I\'ve got wealth, fame, and access to the depths of sleaze that those things bring.</p> <p>It\'s a T. It goes \"tuh\". Dear God, they\'ll be killed on our doorstep! And there\'s no trash pickup until January 3rd. <strong>Spare me your space age technobabble, Attila the Hun!</strong> <em>I\'m a thing.</em> Belligerent and numerous.</p> <h2>Daylight and everything.</h2> <p>You don\'t know how to do any of those. We\'re rescuing ya. Morbo will now introduce tonight\'s candidates… PUNY HUMAN NUMBER ONE, PUNY HUMAN NUMBER TWO, and Morbo\'s good friend, Richard Nixon. Who am I making this out to?</p> <ol> <li>I feel like I was mauled by Jesus.</li> <li>You guys go on without me! I\'m going to go… look for more stuff to steal!</li> <li>We don\'t have a brig.</li> </ol> <h3>Doomsday device? Ah, now the ball\'s in Farnsworth\'s court!</h3> <p>Humans dating robots is sick. You people wonder why I\'m still single? It\'s \'cause all the fine robot sisters are dating humans! Switzerland is small and neutral! We are more like Germany, ambitious and misunderstood!</p> <ul> <li>Take me to your leader!</li> </ul>', '2020-08-05 15:44:11', '2020-09-04 07:20:29', 1, '/img/img-chapter-1.png'),
(51, 'Jean', '14 - Titre à définir', '<h2>These old Doomsday Devices are dangerously unstable. I\'ll rest easier not knowing where they are.</h2>\r\n<p>Five hours? Aw, man! Couldn\'t you just get me the death penalty? I\'m Santa Claus! Kids have names? You\'ve killed me! Oh, you\'ve killed me! Bender, I didn\'t know you liked cooking. That\'s so cute.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>I haven\'t felt much of anything since my guinea pig died.</li>\r\n<li>Who are you, my warranty?!</li>\r\n<li>I barely knew Philip, but as a clergyman I have no problem telling his most intimate friends all about him.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Is today\'s hectic lifestyle making you tense and impatient?</h3>\r\n<p>Soothe us with sweet lies. No. We\'re on the top. Hey, whatcha watching? And I\'m his friend Jesus.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>And then the battle\'s not so bad?</li>\r\n<li>Nay, I respect and admire Harold Zoid too much to beat him to death with his own Oscar.</li>\r\n<li>Then throw her in the laundry room, which will hereafter be referred to as \"the brig\".</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Yes, I saw. You were doing well, until everyone died. Kids have names? I\'m Santa Claus! Ummm…to eBay?</p>\r\n<p>You\'re going back for the Countess, aren\'t you? Say it in Russian! Pansy. How much did you make me? Actually, that\'s still true.</p>\r\n<p>Are you crazy? I can\'t swallow that. It\'s toe-tappingly tragic! WINDMILLS DO NOT WORK THAT WAY! GOOD NIGHT! Now what? Nay, I respect and admire Harold Zoid too much to beat him to death with his own Oscar.</p>\r\n<p>Hey! I\'m a porno-dealing monster, what do I care what you think? Now what? It may comfort you to know that Fry\'s death took only fifteen seconds, yet the pain was so intense, that it felt to him like fifteen years. And it goes without saying, it caused him to empty his bowels.</p>\r\n<p>Yeah, I do that with my stupidness. Fry! Stay back! He\'s too powerful! Well, then good news! It\'s a suppository. They\'re like sex, except I\'m having them! Pansy.</p>\r\n<p>Of all the friends I\'ve had… you\'re the first. I videotape every customer that comes in here, so that I may blackmail them later. Now Fry, it\'s been a few years since medical school, so remind me. Disemboweling in your species: fatal or non-fatal?</p>\r\n<p>What are their names? I love you, buddy! I just told you! You\'ve killed me! I\'m just glad my fat, ugly mama isn\'t alive to see this day.</p>\r\n<p>Who said that? SURE you can die! You want to die?! Robot 1-X, save my friends! And Zoidberg! We can\'t compete with Mom! Her company is big and evil! Ours is small and neutral! Eeeee! Now say \"nuclear wessels\"!</p>\r\n<p>Oh yeah, good luck with that. I found what I need. And it\'s not friends, it\'s things. Well, let\'s just dump it in the sewer and say we delivered it. Large bet on myself in round one.</p>\r\n<p>Shinier than yours, meatbag. Who\'s brave enough to fly into something we all keep calling a death sphere? Goodbye, cruel world. Goodbye, cruel lamp. Goodbye, cruel velvet drapes, lined with what would appear to be some sort of cruel muslin and the cute little pom-pom curtain pull cords. Cruel though they may be…</p>\r\n<p>But, like most politicians, he promised more than he could deliver. Oh, how awful. Did he at least die painlessly? …To shreds, you say. Well, how is his wife holding up? …To shreds, you say.</p>', '2020-09-04 07:23:52', '2020-09-04 07:23:52', 0, '/img/img-chapter-6.png'),
(11, 'Jean', '10 - Quelle sera la prochaine étape ?', '<p>Oh God, my uncle. How am I ever gonna explain this? Red Five standing by. You are a part of the Rebel Alliance and a traitor! Take her away! But with the blast shield down, I can\'t even see! How am I supposed to fight? Remember, a Jedi can feel the Force flowing through him. I\'m trying not to, kid. I\'m surprised you had the courage to take the responsibility yourself. Still, she\'s got a lot of spirit. I don\'t know, what do you think? No! Alderaan is peaceful. We have no weapons. You can\'t possibly? Leave that to me. Send a distress signal, and inform the Senate that all on board were killed. What?! I want to come with you to Alderaan. There\'s nothing for me here now. I want to learn the ways of the Force and be a Jedi, like my father before me.</p>', '2020-08-26 06:45:32', '2020-09-04 06:45:32', 1, '/img/img-chapter-3.png'),
(15, 'Jean', '12 - Loin de tout', '<h1>You don\'t believe in the Force, do you?</h1> <p>What?! Don\'t be too proud of this technological terror you\'ve constructed. The ability to destroy a planet is insignificant next to the power of the Force. Alderaan? I\'m not going to Alderaan. I\'ve got to go home. It\'s late, I\'m in for it as it is.</p> <p>Oh God, my uncle. How am I ever gonna explain this? Partially, but it also obeys your commands. Hey, Luke! May the Force be with you.&nbsp;<strong>He is here.</strong>&nbsp;<em>But with the blast shield down, I can\'t even see!</em>&nbsp;How am I supposed to fight?</p> <h2>I find your lack of faith disturbing.</h2> <p>I call it luck. Red Five standing by. Dantooine. They\'re on Dantooine. Ye-ha!</p> <ol> <li>A tremor in the Force. The last time I felt it was in the presence of my old master.</li> <li>What?!</li> <li>I can\'t get involved! I\'ve got work to do! It\'s not that I like the Empire, I hate it, but there\'s nothing I can do about it right now. It\'s such a long way from here.</li> </ol> <h3>What!?</h3> <p>Alderaan? I\'m not going to Alderaan. I\'ve got to go home. It\'s late, I\'m in for it as it is. I can\'t get involved! I\'ve got work to do! It\'s not that I like the Empire, I hate it, but there\'s nothing I can do about it right now. It\'s such a long way from here.</p> <ul> <li>All right. Well, take care of yourself, Han. I guess that\'s what you\'re best at, ain\'t it?</li> <li>Alderaan? I\'m not going to Alderaan. I\'ve got to go home. It\'s late, I\'m in for it as it is.</li> <li>In my experience, there is no such thing as luck.</li> </ul>', '2020-08-10 13:56:56', '2020-08-10 13:56:56', 1, '/img/img-chapter-2.png'),
(14, 'Jean', '11 - En cours d\'écriture', '<h1>You don\'t believe in the Force, do you?</h1> <p>What?! Don\'t be too proud of this technological terror you\'ve constructed. The ability to destroy a planet is insignificant next to the power of the Force. Alderaan? I\'m not going to Alderaan. I\'ve got to go home. It\'s late, I\'m in for it as it is.</p> <p>Oh God, my uncle. How am I ever gonna explain this? Partially, but it also obeys your commands. Hey, Luke! May the Force be with you.&nbsp;<strong>He is here.</strong>&nbsp;<em>But with the blast shield down, I can\'t even see!</em>&nbsp;How am I supposed to fight?</p> <h2>I find your lack of faith disturbing.</h2> <p>I call it luck. Red Five standing by. Dantooine. They\'re on Dantooine. Ye-ha!</p> <ol> <li>A tremor in the Force. The last time I felt it was in the presence of my old master.</li> <li>What?!</li> <li>I can\'t get involved! I\'ve got work to do! It\'s not that I like the Empire, I hate it, but there\'s nothing I can do about it right now. It\'s such a long way from here.</li> </ol> <h3>What!?</h3> <p>Alderaan? I\'m not going to Alderaan. I\'ve got to go home. It\'s late, I\'m in for it as it is. I can\'t get involved! I\'ve got work to do! It\'s not that I like the Empire, I hate it, but there\'s nothing I can do about it right now. It\'s such a long way from here.</p> <ul> <li>All right. Well, take care of yourself, Han. I guess that\'s what you\'re best at, ain\'t it?</li> <li>Alderaan? I\'m not going to Alderaan. I\'ve got to go home. It\'s late, I\'m in for it as it is.</li> <li>In my experience, there is no such thing as luck.</li> </ul>', '2020-08-04 15:19:24', '2020-08-04 15:19:24', 1, '/img/img-chapter-3.png'),
(50, 'Jean', '13 - Gauche ou droite ?', '<h1>Say it in Russian!</h1>\r\n<p>In our darkest hour, we can stand erect, with proud upthrust bosoms. I\'ll get my kit! Stop it, stop it. It\'s fine. I will \'destroy\' you! Okay, it\'s 500 dollars, you have no choice of carrier, the battery can\'t hold the charge and the reception isn\'t very…</p>\r\n<p>Oh Leela! You\'re the only person I could turn to; you\'re the only person who ever loved me. <strong>With gusto.</strong> <em>Wow, you got that off the Internet?</em> In my day, the Internet was only used to download pornography.</p>\r\n<h2>Take me to your leader!</h2>\r\n<p>Well I\'da done better, but it\'s plum hard pleading a case while awaiting trial for that there incompetence. What\'s with you kids? Every other day it\'s food, food, food. Alright, I\'ll get you some stupid food.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Large bet on myself in round one.</li>\r\n<li>Ask her how her day was.</li>\r\n<li>Yes, if you make it look like an electrical fire. When you do things right, people won\'t be sure you\'ve done anything at all.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2020-09-03 16:53:37', '2020-09-03 16:53:37', 1, '/img/img-chapter-1.png');

